 While Trump called the ad fake, Reagan’s words were real. But context is missing. Here’s a look at the facts: Reagan, who held office during a period of growing fear over Japan’s rising economic might,  made the address  a week after he himself had imposed tariffs on Japanese semiconductors; he was attempting to explain the decision, which seemed at odds with his reputation as a free trader. 

























